.TH SDT-IOCTL 4 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ Devices"
.SH NAME
.B sdt_ioctl
\- Signalling Data Terminal (SDT) 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #include <ss7/lmi.h>
.br
.B #include <ss7/lmi_ioctl.h>
.br
.B #include <ss7/sdli.h>
.br
.B #include <ss7/sdli_ioctl.h>
.br
.B #include <ss7/sdti.h>
.br
.B #include <ss7/sdti_ioctl.h>
.HP
.BI "int " acb56_stream " = open(" \fR/dev/acb56\fI ", " flags );
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B ACB56
is a
Signalling Data Terminal Interface,
.BR sdti (7),
device driver for the SeaLevel Systems, Inc., ACB56 card.
.PP
.B ACB56
is implemented as a
.IR STREAMS (4)
device driver that provides the
Signalling Data Terminal Interface,
.BR sdti (7).
.PP
.B ACB56
provides the following devices that are directly compatible with the stream
types provided by pushing the
.BR sdt (4)
module:
.TP
.I /dev/acb56
This device provides an
.B SDT
protocol service interface using the SDT-primitives of the Signalling Data
Terminal Interface described in
.BR sdti (7).
This interface is suitable for use with the
.BR sl (4)
module for use with the
.BR mtp (4)
or
.BR m2ua (4)
multiplexors.
.SH IOCTLS
.PP
All interfaces support a set of Local Management Interface IO controls,
.BR lmi_ioctl (4),
using the
.BR ioctl (2)
and
.I I_STR
command to the
.BR streamio (2)
system call on the
.I acb56_stream
file descriptor.
See
.BR sdt_ioctl (4)
for a complete description of SDT management controls, and
below for a description of SDT management controls particular to the
.B ACB56
driver.
.SS Configuration
.PP
Confiruation management IO controls use the
.B sdt_config
structure described in
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
The
.B sdt_config
structure contains the following members:
.TP
.I t8
T8 timeout.
.TP
.I Tin
AERM normal proving threshold.
.TP
.I Tie
AERM emergency proving threshold.
.TP
.I T
SUERM error threshold.
.TP
.I D
SUERM error rate parameter.
.TP
.I Te
EIM error threshold.
.TP
.I De
EIM correct decrement.
.TP
.I Ue
EIM error increment.
.TP
.I N
Octets per su in octet-counting mode.
.TP
.I m
Maximum SIF size.
.TP
.I b
Transmit block size.
.TP
.I f
Number of flags between frames
.RS
.TP
.B SDT_FLAGS_ONE
.TP
.B SDT_FLAGS_SHARED
.TP
.B SDT_FLAGS_TWO
.TP
.B SDT_FLAGS_THREE
.RE
.IP \(em 4
.B ACB56
does not support the flags,
.IR f ,
field of the
.B sdt_config
structure.  The number of flags between frames is under the control of the SCC
chip on the card.
.IP \(em
.B ACB56
does not support the transmit block size,
.IR b ,
field of the
.B sdt_config
structure.
.IP \(em
.B ACB56
does not support the following fields
of the
.B sdt_config
structure:
.IR t8 ,
.IR Te ,
.IR De " and "
.IR Ue ,
as it does not support high speed links.

.SS Options
.PP
Options management IO controls use the
.B sdt_opt_conf
structure described in
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
The
.B sdt_opt_conf
structure contains the following members:
.TP
.I pvar
Protocol variant.
.RS
.PP
.B SS7_PVAR_ITUT_88
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ITUT_93
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ITUT_96
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ITUT_00
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ETSI_88
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ETSI_93
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ETSI_96
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ETSI_00
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ANSI_88
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ANSI_92
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ANSI_96
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_ANSI_00
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_JTTC_94
.br
.B SS7_PVAR_CHIN_00
.RE
.TP
.I popt
Protocol options.
.RS
.TP
.B SS7_POPT_MPLEV
Multiple priority/congestion levels.
.TP
.B SS7_POPT_PCR
Preventative cyclic retranlmission.
.TP
.B SS7_POPT_HSL
High speed links.
.TP
.B SS7_POPT_XSN
Extended sequence numbers.
.TP
.B SS7_POPT_ALL
All options.
.RE
.IP \(em 4
.B ACB56
does not support the protocol options
.BR SS7_POPT_HSL ,
.BR SS7_POPT_XSN  " and "
.BR SS7_POPT_ALL ,
values in the
.I popt
field of the
.B sdt_opt_conf
structure, as it does not support high speed links.
.SS State
.PP
State management IO controls use the
.B sdt_statem
structure described in
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
The
.B sdt_statem
structure contains the following members:
.TP
.I aerm_state
AERM state variable
.TP
.I aborted_proving
AERM aborted proving
.TP
.I Ca
AERM error counter
.TP
.I Ti
AERM threshold
.TP
.I suerm_state
SUERM state variable
.TP
.I Cs
SUERM error counter
.TP
.I Ns
SUERM su counter
.TP
.I eim_state
EIM state variable
.TP
.I Ce
EIM counter
.TP
.I su_received
EIM su received flag
.TP
.I interval_error
EIM interval error flag
.TP
.I daedt_state
DAEDT state variable
.RS
.TP
.B SDT_STATE_IDLE
.TP
.B SDT_STATE_IN_SERVICE
.TP
.B SDT_STATE_MONITORING
.TP
.B SDT_STATE_CONGESTED
.RE
.TP
.I daedr_state
DAEDR state variable
.TP
.I octet_counting_mode
Receivers freewheeling.
.IP \(em 4
.B ACB56
does not support the
.IR eim_state ,
.IR Ce ,
.IR su_received " or "
.IR interval_error ,
fields of the
.B sdt_statem
structure, as it does not support high speed links.
.SS Statistics
.PP
Statistics management IO controls use the
.B sdt_stats
structure described in
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
The
.B sdt_stats
structure contains the following members:
.TP
.I header
.TP
.I tx_bytes
.TP
.I tx_sus
.TP
.I tx_sus_repeated
.TP
.I tx_underruns
.TP
.I tx_aborts
.TP
.I tx_buffer_overflows
.TP
.I tx_sus_in_error
.TP
.I rx_bytes
.TP
.I rx_sus
.TP
.I rx_sus_compressed
.TP
.I rx_overruns
.TP
.I rx_aborts
.TP
.I rx_buffer_overflows
.TP
.I rx_sus_in_error
.TP
.I rx_sync_transitions
.TP
.I rx_bits_octet_counted
.TP
.I rx_crc_errors
.TP
.I rx_frame_errors
.TP
.I rx_frame_overflows
.TP
.I rx_frame_too_long
.TP
.I rx_frame_too_short
.TP
.I rx_residue_errors
.TP
.I rx_length_error
.TP
.I carrier_cts_lost
.TP
.I carrier_dcd_lost
.TP
.I carrier_lost
.IP \(em 4
.B ACB56
does not support the
.I carrier_lost
field of the
.B sdt_stats
structure, as it does not support common carrier modes.
.SS Events
.PP
Event management IO controls use the
.B sdt_notify
structure described in
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
The
.B sdt_notify
structure contains the following members:
.TP
.I events
.RS
.TP
.B SDT_EVT_LOST_SYNC
The link has lost synchronization with flags.
.TP
.B SDT_EVT_SU_ERROR
The link has received an SU in error.
.TP
.B SDT_EVT_TX_FAIL
Tx failure has been detected.
.TP
.B SDT_EVT_RX_FAIL
Rx failure has been detected.
.TP
.B SDT_EVT_CARRIER
Carrier failure has been detected.
.RE
.SS Commands
.PP
Command management IO controls use the
.B sdt_mgmt
structure described in
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
The
.B sdt_mgmt
structure contains the following members:
.PP
There are no commands for
.BR sdt_ioctl (4).
